This paper deals with the optimization of modulation schemes for satellite broadcasting, which falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT). The use of genetic algorithms for optimization suggests a focus on networking and communication (cs.NI) subfield. The paper also discusses the use of hierarchical modulation, which is a technique used in distributed computing (cs.DC) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions perceptual quality measurements, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
